\chapter{Other Nonfunctional Requirements}
\section{Performance Requirements}
\begin{itemize}
    \item The website will load in less than 2 seconds. 
    \item The website should be able to support up to 75 concurrent users at a time. 
    \item The website should be able to handle 1000 registered users.
    \item The website should maintain a 99 percent up-time.
\end{itemize}

\section{Safety Requirements}
\begin{itemize}
    \item BurnLab will display a disclaimer stating that it is not a substitute for medical or professional healthcare advice. Users are encouraged to consult a physician before starting any fitness or nutrition plan.
    \item An allergy and dietary restriction filter will be provided to help prevent accidental exposure to harmful ingredients.
    \item The system will implement validation checks to reduce errors in financial transactions and order processing, ensuring that users are not mistakenly charged.
    \item In case of system failures, users will be redirected to an error page with safe recovery options (e.g., retry or cancel actions) to prevent data corruption.
\end{itemize}

\section{Security Requirements}
\textit{
    \begin{itemize}
        \item All communications between client and server will use HTTPS with TLS encryption. 
        \item \textit{User authentication will require strong passwords (minimum 8 characters, including numbers, special characters, and mixed case).}
        \item Passwords will be stored using industry-standard hashing (e.g., bcrypt or SHA-256 with salt).
        \item The system will enforce automatic logout after a defined period of inactivity (e.g., 15 minutes).
        \item Sensitive data such as credit card numbers will never be stored in plain text and will comply with PCI DSS standards.\textit{}
        \item Only authorized administrators will have access to seller and buyer data.}
    \end{itemize}

\section{Software Quality Attributes}

    \item \textbf{Usability:} The platform will prioritize a clean and intuitive interface so new users can navigate with minimal instruction.
    \item \textbf{Reliability:} BurnLab will aim for 99\% uptime and include backup procedures to recover from unexpected crashes.
    \item \textbf{Maintainability:} The system codebase will follow modular design and documentation standards so future developers can easily update or fix issues.
    \item \textbf{Scalability:} The architecture will be designed to scale from supporting hundreds of users to thousands without significant degradation in performance.
    \item \textbf{Portability:} The platform will be accessible on major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari) and responsive on both desktop and mobile devices.
    \item \textbf{Testability:} Features will be implemented with automated unit and integration tests to verify correctness.$>$}

\chapter{Other Requirements}
\textbf{Database Requirements}: The system will maintain user accounts, profiles, order histories, and product listings in a secure relational database
\textbf{Legal Requirements:} The platform must comply with GDPR (for EU users), CCPA (for California users), and other relevant data privacy regulations.
